Nothing can stop this feeling that I have.
Not the cutting of the grass,
Nor the destruction of a building.

No one can stop the emotions inside me.
Not the little child on the corner of the street,
Nor the president of the United States.

This is something that I own,
Something you cannot take away.
And that is that, but this is real.

Nothing can stop this feeling that I have.
Not the singing of a bird,
Nor the starting of a bloody war.

No one can stop the emotions inside me.
Not the parents that raised me,
Nor the all seeing power above us.

The power of this emotion,
Is something that I own.
It will not change and it cannot change.

This is something that I own,
Something you cannot take away.
And that is that, but this is real.

There's a force in this world that overcomes your body and you wont even know it until you get that assurance from another being. It builds up so much force and intensity in your innards even though you know that it's not possible for it to do so. Your body goes into small quick convulsions, your palms produce salt water, your heart beats quicken as if you just ran a mile in under four minutes, and your stomach spreads its wings and attempts to release itself by ripping through your flesh. Sometimes you find yourself starring at the smallest things and thinking about what they must feel and if they can feel this force as well. Or maybe you like to stare out into the sky and imagine seeing it transfer between the stars and shooting back into the crowns of another human. Or maybe, just maybe, you don't believe in it at all. You think it's something society created to develop healthy home lives and premarital sex. Whatever it may be, we all know it exists and it is captivated in the eyes and the bodies of the world. Now, I dare you to experience this force with no regrets. Can you handle it?

so basically.. Linda and I skipped the whole day of school. We went to a cemetery for a bit and she hated the orange she was eating so she threw it on the grass and made awesome flower crowns for her and I. Then we walked to a beach by the marina where I went in the cold water up to my knees and then we wrote a message in a bottle and put our secrets in it and Linda got mad because I suggested that we use her Poland Springs bottle and she dumped out all the water. Then we went to another cemetery by a church on main st and laid under a huge pine tree and talked about such and such and I made a tee-pee out of sticks for her to live in. Then we met up with Matt at the marina and he informed us to go hide because the tennis team was going to nantucket so we ran behind some stupid tourist attraction. When he returned we fed the geese and one bit my finger.. but thats okay I still love it. And some creepy guy asked us to trade him 2 bucks for a bag of chips so he could get clams.. I dont know WHY so we did. Then after matt left Linda and I went to the mall via Bbus and we chilled in Barns and Noble for a tad and then we went to spencers and then we went to those photo booths that you get a strip of photos for three dollars. well we didnt have three dollars so we sat in there and took our own pictures :). then we waited for the bus to come outside the mall and it was 20 minutes late and that sucked. but all an all it was AMAZING <3 Linda made awesome flower-child crowns :) "I am just a speck of dust inside a giants eye" We gonna git youuuz. CHEEEZEUMZ make a wish. 3 dollahz aint no thang.

I'm really starting to HATE people. Just everything about us is so fucked up. Not just our form and the reason we're on this earth, It's the way we express the reason why we're on this earth. At this age, being a teenager is just like being a blind man in an art museum; life doesn't make any sense. We think we "know" our surroundings and we think we've found ourselves and that we're on the top of the universe. Well we're obviously wrong. There's people out there that CRAVE attention but dont want to admit it to themselves. Hopefully they'll change in a couple years and be like "Fuck I was such a douchebag!". They search for attention in numerous ways but the most common are: 1. Lying their fucking ass off so people will feel bad for them. Like faking some sort of serious illness (cancer for example) or a serious drug addiction like heroine. These people also like to talk shit about others behind their backs and expect them not to get angry. Fuckers. 2. There's some people that I care about in my life but they go waaaay too fucking overboard with their actions. They try to make themselves as noticeable as possible as a sign of rebellion even though they know they look like absolute shit and are just trying to "get back" at their parents. And while they're telling you about how horrible it is because their mother wont let them wear makeup or nailpolish they dont realize that they could be talking to someone who has it five hundred times worse than them. 3. Sitting all alone away from their friends quietly writing in a notebook. People usually think that they really do wanna be alone but they really dont. They want someone to come over to them and ask them whats wrong. And after denying that nothings wrong about 5 times they finally make up something fucking stupid to say so the other person feels bad for them. Ridiculous? I think so. IF YOU EVER FIND SOMEONE WITH ALL THESE THREE CHARACTERISTICS... MORE POWER TO YA! And just the FACT that people make fun of their own kind for "amusement" or because they have nothing better to do sickens the fuck out of me. Speaking your mind is a totally different thing. If someone asked me what I thought of a fucking stupid situation.. I'd tell them that they're fucking stupid. Getting back to the making fun thing.. Its horrible for people to make fun of others especially if that person cannot stick up for themselves. Spreading rumors is another fucking thing that pisses me off. what's in a rumor?! All they do is fly around the school whispering in other's ears while carefully sticking pins into a voodoo doll of the rumored person. fuck that. ... I guess my rant is over, but I'll probably add alot more to this later on.
